      "name": "Customer Service Sample Roleplay 2",
      "event": "Customer Service",
      "prompt": "Background: You are a Customer Care Representative within the Membership Department of the FBLA National Center. You handle all calls related to membership benefits, renewals, and contact information updates. You field an average of 100 calls per day. During each call, you need to verify the caller\u2019s current contact information prior to answering any questions.\n\nScenario: It is important to be aware of the various levels of FBLA and the benefits provided for each division. Your goal is to update the caller\u2019s contact information, understand their request and needs, and prescribe various options available to them as current and past FBLA members. The judges are all past FBLA members from different chapters and now work for the same company. During a recent lunch outing, the discussion came up about wanting to volunteer their time and support to local FBLA chapters in their area. You should provide information about the FBLA Alumni Professional Network. You will be fielding a call from a past FBLA member (judges). You should \u201canswer the call\u201d with the following greeting: \u201cFBLA National Center, this is _______ (your name). How may I help you?\u201d Other Useful Information Communicate the benefits of membership. Provide ways to contact state and local chapters. Explain the type of opportunities where volunteers are needed such as coaching, judging, mentors, and fundraising.\n\nThings To Consider: You must present strategies/solutions to address the client\u2019s questions during the simulated telephone conversation. You must address the following in your presentation: The scenario and the scope involved. Your position and why. Effective solutions for meeting the caller\u2019s needs.",
