      "prompt": "Background: As a client service representative in the asphalt industry, you often work with familiar clients. Your company is a supplier of aggregates (rocks) to the asphalt producer plants. Aggregates are a crucial component to make asphalt. Your company\u2019s supply is quarried from a large river system. Due to a large rain system and unprecedented flooding, your company is five days behind on supply.\n\nScenario: The largest asphalt customer (judges) must be notified of the lack of aggregate supply and you have been tasked with that responsibility. Asphalt production relies completely on aggregate supply so the customer\u2019s work will be impacted by this issue. As a client service representative, you must develop a plan to maintain a positive relationship with the client, explain the current situation, create a timeline for supply restock, offer alternatives to supply and/or a reduction in fees. Your goal is to communicate effectively with the customer and provide a report to internal team members. OBJECTIVES OF THE ROLE PLAY The competitor(s) must address the following during the role play: Build and maintain relationships with customers Interpret business policies to customers/clients Work closely with clients and all departments to ensure accurate and timely resolution of customer questions, concerns, or issues Evaluate supply and demand issues Handle customer/client complaints Understands the techniques and strategies used to foster positive, ongoing relationships with customers",
