      "prompt": "Background: As a client service representative for a plastics company, you are meeting with a large restaurant chain that specializes in fast food hamburgers, sodas, and milkshakes. Your company is a supplier of to-go drink cups and packaging items. Your drink cups are thermoformed cups and can be printed to include a company\u2019s logo or special marketing initiatives.\n\nScenario: You are meeting with a marketing team from the restaurant chain (judges). You want to sell them on the concept of a holiday edition of your to-go cups customized for them. You must meet with the team and develop three ideas to take back to your design team for samples. Your goal is to maintain the relationship with the client while encouraging them to add the additional purchase. Additionally, you will follow up with them on their regular purchased cups to make sure they are happy with the product, supply, and services. Your goal is to communicate effectively with the customer, sell the concept of holiday cups, create three design ideas, and provide a report to internal team members. OBJECTIVES OF THE ROLE PLAY The competitor(s) must address the following during the role play: Build and maintain relationships with customers. Interpret business policies to customers/clients. Work closely with clients and all departments to ensure accurate and timely resolution of customer questions, concerns, or issues. Evaluate supply and demand issues. Develop new strands of business. Understands the techniques and strategies used to foster positive, ongoing relationships with customers.",
