      "prompt": "Background: You are developing a lawn mowing company for your medium size community. You have a handful of clients in your neighborhood but want to work up to 45 clients per week. The business will be staffed by you and one additional person. You currently have adequate equipment for starting the company and will not have to purchase any equipment for at least two years. You are located in the Midwest area of the country. This location indicates lawn services are typically needed once a week between the months of April to October and monthly check-ins November to March. Additionally, average pricing for a \u00bd acre yard is $50 per service.\n\nScenario: You are meeting with a Homeowner\u2019s Association (HOA) board (the judges). You are seeking a contract from them for common spaces (4 acres of common space) in their community and advertising in their community newsletter. For this meeting, please present the following information about your company. Your vision and mission statement. Your timeline for lawn services. Information about insurance coverage and safety precautions. Plan for quality control of all areas under contract. Pricing strategy for contract. Any additional information that would be pertinent for the HOA to know or would help secure the contract. OBJECTIVES OF THE ROLE PLAY The competitor(s) must address the following during the role play: Create a company vision and mission statement. Define the industry characteristics, major competitors, and market segment. Apply strategies for determining and adjusting prices to maximize return and meet customers\u2019 perceptions of value. Prepare a management plan that incorporates legal requirements and insurance. Prepare a management plan that includes quality control.",
