      "name": "Hospitality & Event Management Sample Roleplay 8",
      "event": "Hospitality & Event Management",
      "prompt": "Background: The Ocean Pointe Resort, a coastal resort located in Hilton Head, South Carolina, experienced declining guest satisfaction and occupancy rates over the past two years. The resort, which includes 300 rooms, a convention center, three restaurants, and beachfront amenities, decided to launch a strategic revitalization project to reposition itself as a top-tier destination for both leisure and business travelers.\n\nScenario: A cross-functional leadership team was appointed to overhaul the resort\u2019s operations, branding, and guest experience. Your task is to present ways to focus on the guest experience. You must prepare a plan considering the marketing, operational, and event management strategies to work towards a goal of a 25% increase in guest satisfaction within 18 months. You will present your portion of the plan to the leadership team (judges). OBJECTIVES OF THE ROLE PLAY The competitor(s) must address the following during the role play: Explain public relations and publicity as they relate to the hospitality industry. Explain the role of demographics as it relates to hospitality management. Describe property wide amenities that meet the needs of the different target markets in the hospitality industry. Describe incentives and rewards for long-term repeat individuals/groups in the hospitality industry. Describe the value of customer feedback in the hospitality industry as it relates to improvement to product and service. Describe hotel in-room amenities and explain why they are important to guests. Describe property wide hotel amenities and explain why they are important to guests. Explain typical rating systems used in the lodging business. Conduct research to determine customer needs and wants in the hospitality industry.",
