      "name": "International Business Sample Roleplay 7",
      "event": "International Business",
      "prompt": "Background: You are the HR Manager for a multinational company that works in textile research and production. The company operates in several countries and territories including the United States, the European Union, India, and Colombia. Cultural differences, social expectations, and local labor laws can influence the HR functions of your company and vary globally.\n\nScenario: You have been asked by leadership to assess and revise the company\u2019s global HR practices around two key initiatives. The key initiatives focus on health and safety in the workplace and employee motivation. Both categories can vary greatly with expectations between cultures. You must develop a list of three goals for each initiative to share with leadership (the judges) at a team meeting. Be sure to consider what information and research is needed to adequately address these goals.\n\nObjectives: You must address the following during the role play: Describe the different living and working conditions found in various countries. Assess how social and cultural factors influence the human resource functions (e.g., recruitment selection; employee development; evaluation; compensation, promotion, benefit, and incentives; and separation, termination, and transition). Identify how motivational techniques for workers may differ when used in different cultures. Assess the impact of various occupational health and safety standards on conducting international business. Explain the advantages and disadvantages of a company having access to a global labor pool.",
