      "name": "Sports & Entertainment Management Sample Roleplay 7",
      "event": "Sports & Entertainment Management",
      "prompt": "Background: You work for a large multi-use arena in a city with a strong sports tourism industry. The venue is used primarily for basketball games but also has a large outdoor venue and is in the middle of the entertainment district. The venue seats 25,000 for a basketball game. There will be events for the tournament at five other locations. Representatives from your arena are also on a city-wide sports tourism team to help make the overall experience and event successful. The event will be attended by many out of town guests so the related activities and overall safety and success of the event is important.\n\nScenario: Your venue is going to be part of a city-wide national college basketball tournament. The tournament will take place over two weekends. You are tasked with developing a recruitment and retention strategy for employees and volunteers to staff this event and future events of a similar status. The strategy should focus on attaining the required number of employees needed and how to maintain temporary employees for special events. You are also part of a city-wide committee to recruit volunteers to help with the tournament and provide support in the entertainment district. Finally, include an approach to provide an effective job orientation to prepare people for their roles. OBJECTIVES OF THE ROLE PLAY The competitor(s) must address the following during the role play: Describe strategies to recruit sports and entertainment employees. Describe the recruiting and retention processes. Explain the importance of job orientation. Employ the principles of safety to sports and entertainment. Assess demographic and geographic considerations related to sports and entertainment.",
